Saturday’s torrential rainfall in Lagos has wreaked havoc in Magodo, Kosofe Local Government Area of the state. DAILY POST gathered that a building collapsed early morning in Orisha community in the area, traping four persons to death. The victims are reportedly of the same family. Emergency workers are currently at the scene carrying out rescue and evacuation. Details later… Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.